                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14141233" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 20:24:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t truncate hints or batchlog, but both look at the truncation records when deciding whether or not to replay a particular mutation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14141238" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 20:26:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Which is probably what paxos should be doing too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14221199" author="beobal" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2014 18:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch to ensure we update persisted paxos state whether we actually apply or drop the commit &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14222984" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2014 13:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
